data.title: Twenty One Pilots Release New Single ‘Next Semester’
data.meta_description: Twenty One Pilots have just dropped the punk-infused, garage rock track ‘Next Semester’, the second single from their upcoming new album ‘Clancy’.
data.text:
Twenty One Pilots have just dropped the punk-infused, garage rock track ‘Next Semester’, the second single from their upcoming new album ‘Clancy’.

The new track comes with a music video that sees the band performing for a packed crowd in a tiny club with the band sharing that they simply “Cannot wait to sing this one with you.”

Watch the video for ‘Next Semester’ below:

‘Clancy’ is out on May 17 via Fueled By Ramen and also includes the previous single ‘Overcompensate’. The band have also just announced the ‘Clancy World Tour’ and you can get all the details and dates on that right here.

Twenty One Pilots’ Tyler Joseph and Josh Dun are the latest winners of our Rock Sound 25 Icon Award, returning to the cover of the magazine as we continue to celebrate our 25th anniversary.
